    "explanationB": "Correct. Targeted modulation of dopaminergic signaling across motor and limbic tracts is the cornerstone of Parkinson's therapy. The nigrostriatal pathway (motor) and mesolimbic pathway (mood/motivation) both rely on adequate dopamine — explaining both motor symptoms and the neuropsychiatric features of PD.",
    "explanationC": "Nicotinic agonism at the NMJ causes muscle contraction — a peripheral mechanism unrelated to the central dopaminergic deficiency that underlies parkinsonian motor symptoms.",
