    "explanationB": "Correct. Sumatriptan's 5-HT1B/1D agonism provides migraine-specific relief through cranial vasoconstriction (1B) and trigeminal neuropeptide release inhibition (1D). This explains both efficacy and cardiovascular contraindications — vasoconstriction is therapeutic in cranial but dangerous in coronary vessels.",
    "explanationC": "IL-5 neutralization (mepolizumab) targets eosinophilic inflammation in severe asthma — a fundamentally different pathway from the serotonergic trigeminovascular circuit targeted by triptans.",
