    "rationale": "MOA DETAIL: The INCRETIN AXIS: GLP-1 (glucagon-like peptide-1) and GIP (glucose-dependent insulinotropic peptide) are gut hormones released after eating. GLP-1 RECEPTOR AGONISTS (semaglutide, liraglutide) mimic GLP-1 with enhanced half-life. Effects: (1) GLUCOSE-DEPENDENT insulin secretion (low hypoglycemia risk), (2) glucagon suppression, (3) delayed gastric emptying, (4) central appetite suppression → weight loss 10-15%, (5) cardiovascular protection (SUSTAIN-6, SELECT). DPP-4 INHIBITORS (sitagliptin) prevent GLP-1 degradation — less potent than exogenous GLP-1 RAs. Never combine GLP-1 RA + DPP-4 inhibitor (redundant).\n\nKEY MEDICATIONS: semaglutide, liraglutide, dulaglutide, exenatide, sitagliptin, saxagliptin\n\nCLINICAL APPLICATION: Within Endocrine, this scenario is best explained by glucose-dependent insulin support with counter-regulatory suppression.",
