    "explanationC": "DNA gyrase inhibition is an antimicrobial mechanism.",
    "explanationD": "NMJ agonism has no role in iron absorption or hematopoiesis.",
    "examTip": "Oral iron: take on empty stomach with vitamin C for best absorption. GI side effects (nausea, constipation, dark stools) common — limit adherence. Separate from PPIs, antacids, calcium, tetracyclines, levothyroxine by 2+ hours. IV iron: anaphylaxis risk (test dose for iron dextran; newer formulations safer). Iron studies: ferritin (<30 = deficient), TIBC (elevated in deficiency), transferrin saturation (<20% = functional deficiency).",
