    "explanationA": "COX inhibition is an anti-inflammatory mechanism unrelated to bacterial cell wall synthesis.",
    "explanationB": "Correct. Beta-lactam antibiotics are bactericidal through PBP-mediated interruption of peptidoglycan cross-linking. Understanding this shared mechanism explains cross-reactivity patterns, resistance mechanisms (beta-lactamases, altered PBPs like MRSA's PBP2a), and the rationale for beta-lactamase inhibitor combinations.",
