    "examTip": "Penicillin allergy: ~10% cross-reactivity with cephalosporins (lower with 3rd/4th-gen). MRSA: altered PBP2a (mecA gene) → resistant to ALL beta-lactams except ceftaroline. Carbapenem resistance (CRE): carbapenemases → treat with ceftazidime-avibactam or meropenem-vaborbactam. Ampicillin + amoxicillin: Listeria coverage. Ceftriaxone: avoid in neonates (bilirubin displacement).",
