    "examTip": "Naloxone: titrate to respiratory effort (not full consciousness — to avoid acute opioid withdrawal with vomiting, agitation, pulmonary edema). Fentanyl overdose may need HIGHER and REPEATED naloxone doses (high receptor affinity). Flumazenil: CONTRAINDICATED in chronic BZD users (withdrawal seizures) and mixed overdoses with pro-convulsants. All overdose patients need observation period matching the offending drug's duration.",
